    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="[November 2, Idleb] The director of Al-Mafraq camp in northern Idlib, Abu Nawaf, explains that the amount of water available per person ranges between 30 or 35 liters per day.&#10;For bathing days, the available quantities of water become greater, and the water allocated to one family is barely enough, which causes a crisis that leads families to rationing the use of water, according to Mustafa Ali Al-Muhammad, who is displaced from the countryside of Maarat al-Numan.&#10;The director of the &quot;Syria Response Coordinators&quot; team, Muhammad Hallaj, told the &quot;Syria TV&quot; website that the lack of water in the camps is one of the main reasons for the spread of Corona virus among the displaced."/>
